Class Scene

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.carnivorous_exports.pix.Scene

  • public class Scene
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains the methods that draw the scene, assign textures and materials of objects, and check for collision detection.

      • getCubeList

        public int getCubeList(javax.media.opengl.GL2 gl,
              java.lang.String textureFileName,
              java.lang.String textureFileType)
        This method returns a display list for a cube with a specific texture. Display lists can let you replace all the vertex calls for an object with one line. It's especially useful if you have to draw many of the same kind of primitive object.
        Parameters:
        gl - the current GL
        textureFileName - the path to the texture file
        textureFileType - the type of file that the texture file is (.jpg, .png, etc)
        Returns:
        the display list

      • loadTexture

      • drawScene

        public void drawScene(javax.media.opengl.GL2 gl,
             int[] displayList,
             int i)
        This method lays out everything in the scene. In this case, it's only a cube and a sphere. If the objects have to be picked, they also have to be named too.
        Parameters:
        gl - the current GL
        displayList - an array of the display lists (of cubes with different textures)
        i - the texture that the cube should be

      • hasCollided

        public float[] hasCollided(float[] cube1,
                  float cube1Length,
                  float[] cube2,
                  float cube2Length)
        Determines whether a cube has collided with another cube
        Parameters:
        cube1 - the 3D position of the first cube
        cube1Length - the length of one side of the first cube
        cube2 - the 3D position of the second cube
        cube2Length - the length of one side of the second cube
        Returns:
        An array with the respective reaction an object should take. If the objects did not collide, there is no reaction.

        Parameters:
